Creating the SpriteBatch in the constructor method right after the GraphicsDeviceManager throws an exception.

``` C#
public GameScreen()
{
    graphics = new GraphicsDeviceManager(this);
    spritebatch = new SpriteBatch(GraphicsDevice);
}
```

Does MonoGame allows this? Then a workaround must be found to correct this (e.g. update the GraphicsDeviceManager earlier so the object state is available).

Otherwise if it's not allowed then a meaningful exception message could be written so user can be informed about the situation.
(i.e. Please initialize SpriteBatch only on LoadContent method)

Thanks.

P.S. File of interest is here:
MonoGame.Framework\Graphics\SpriteBatch.cs Line 39

So I do not forgot about https://github.com/mono/MonoGame/issues/3624 and finally released it.
